From 64a3f5f2d3ead1d4932394e15053345914352631 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: WimLee115 <wimlee@>
Date: Mon, 16 Feb 2026 16:33:47 +0100
Subject: Fix monitor mode kernel panic under load: race condition &
 double-free

Kernel panic when capturing packets in monitor mode under high load
(fern-wifi-cracker, airodump-ng). Three issues fixed:

(a) rx_req->os_priv not cleared after ownership transfer to recv_frame,
    leaving stale pointer that phl_recycle_rx_pkt_usb could double-free
(b) No netif_running() check - interface teardown during packet processing
    could deliver to torn-down netdev
(c) RTW_CANNOT_RUN check after expensive skb_copy_expand instead of before

Also increased SKB headroom from 64 to 128 bytes for safety margin over
the 52-byte max radiotap header. Updated README to document patch #11.

